cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "kfda-mcp: MCP Server for Korean MFDS Public APIs"
abstract: >
  An open-source MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that wraps the Korean
  Ministry of Food and Drug Safety (MFDS, 식약처) public OpenAPIs, enabling
  LLM agents (Claude, GPT, etc.) to autonomously query Korean drug master,
  DUR (Drug Utilization Review) safety rules, e약은요 patient-friendly drug
  information, and functional health food (건강기능식품) data through the
  standard Anthropic MCP protocol. This is the first MCP server published
  for the Korean MFDS healthcare data ecosystem.
